{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":891,"text":"Is there a real you?"},{"time":1988,"text":"This might seem to you \nlike a very odd question."},{"time":4338,"text":"Because, you might ask,"},{"time":6897,"text":"how do we find the real you,"},{"time":9225,"text":"how do you know what the real you is?"},{"time":11259,"text":"And so forth."}]},{"cues":[{"time":12223,"text":"But the idea that there must be a real you,"},{"time":15591,"text":"surely that's obvious."},{"time":16634,"text":"If there's anything real \nin the world, it's you."},{"time":19895,"text":"Well, I'm not quite sure."},{"time":21840,"text":"At least we have to understand \na bit better what that means."},{"time":24457,"text":"Now certainly, I think there are\nlots of things in our culture around us"},{"time":28291,"text":"which sort of reinforce the idea"},{"time":30498,"text":"that for each one of us,\nwe have a kind of a core, an essence."},{"time":34249,"text":"There is something about what it means\nto be you which defines you,"},{"time":37683,"text":"and it's kind of permanent and unchanging."},{"time":40003,"text":"The most kind of crude way\nin which we have it,"},{"time":41813,"text":"are things like horoscopes."},{"time":43107,"text":"You know, people are very wedded\nto these, actually."},{"time":46147,"text":"People put them on their Facebook profile"},{"time":48111,"text":"as though they are meaningul,"},{"time":49594,"text":"you even know \nyour Chinese horoscope as well."},{"time":52271,"text":"There are also \nmore scientific versions of this,"},{"time":54724,"text":"all sorts of ways of profiling\npersonality type,"},{"time":57781,"text":"such as the Myers-Briggs tests,\nfor example."},{"time":60454,"text":"I don't know if you've done those."},{"time":61835,"text":"A lot of companies \nuse these for recruitment."},{"time":63739,"text":"You answer a lot of questions,"},{"time":67036,"text":"and this is supposed to reveal\nsomething about your core personality."},{"time":70792,"text":"And of course, the popular fascination \nwith this is enormous."},{"time":74093,"text":"In magazines like this, you'll see,"},{"time":75761,"text":"in the bottom left corner,\nthey'll advertise in virtually every issue"},{"time":79223,"text":"some kind of personality thing."},{"time":81333,"text":"And if you pick up one of those magazines,"},{"time":83113,"text":"it's hard to resist, isn't it?"},{"time":84361,"text":"Doing the test to find\nwhat is your learning style,"},{"time":87226,"text":"what is your loving style,\nor what is your working style?"},{"time":90354,"text":"Are you this kind of person or that?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":92954,"text":"So I think that we have a common-sense idea"},{"time":96987,"text":"that there is a kind of core \nor essence of ourselves"},{"time":99634,"text":"to be discovered."},{"time":101168,"text":"And that this is kind of a permanent truth\nabout ourselves,"},{"time":104424,"text":"something that's the same throughout life."},{"time":106864,"text":"Well, that's the idea I want to challenge."},{"time":110615,"text":"And I have to say now,\nI'll say it a bit later,"},{"time":112457,"text":"but I'm not challenging this\njust because I'm weird,"},{"time":115285,"text":"the challenge actually has a very,\nvery long and distinguished history."},{"time":119082,"text":"Here's the common-sense idea."},{"time":121251,"text":"There is you."},{"time":122287,"text":"You are the individuals you are,\nand you have this kind of core."},{"time":125595,"text":"Now in your life, what happens\nis that you, of course,"},{"time":130227,"text":"accumulate different experiences\nand so forth."},{"time":132446,"text":"So you have memories,"},{"time":134716,"text":"and these memories help \nto create what you are."},{"time":136966,"text":"You have desires, maybe for a cookie,"},{"time":139623,"text":"maybe for something\nthat we don't want to talk about"},{"time":142418,"text":"at 11 o'clock in the morning\nin a school."},{"time":144293,"text":"You will have beliefs."},{"time":146274,"text":"This is a number plate\nfrom someone in America."},{"time":148187,"text":"I don't know whether this number plate,\nwhich says \"messiah 1,\""},{"time":150959,"text":"indicates that the driver\nbelieves in the messiah,"},{"time":153251,"text":"or that they are the messiah."},{"time":155445,"text":"Either way, they have beliefs \nabout messiahs."},{"time":158158,"text":"We have knowledge."},{"time":159620,"text":"We have sensations and experiences as well."},{"time":161878,"text":"It's not just intellectual things."},{"time":164395,"text":"So this is kind of \nthe common-sense model, I think,"},{"time":166998,"text":"of what a person is."},{"time":168150,"text":"There is a person who has all the things\nthat make up our life experiences."}]},{"cues":[{"time":174441,"text":"But the suggestion \nI want to put to you today"},{"time":176960,"text":"is that there's something \nfundamentally wrong with this model."},{"time":180395,"text":"And I can show you what's wrong\nwith one click."},{"time":182853,"text":"Which is there isn't actually a \"you\"\nat the heart of all these experiences."},{"time":189708,"text":"Strange thought?\nWell, maybe not."},{"time":191321,"text":"What is there, then?"},{"time":193079,"text":"Well, clearly there are memories,\ndesires, intentions, sensations,"},{"time":196348,"text":"and so forth."},{"time":198291,"text":"But what happens is\nthese things exist,"},{"time":200549,"text":"and they're kind of all integrated,"},{"time":202618,"text":"they're overlapped, they're connected\nin various different ways."},{"time":206407,"text":"They're connecting partly,\nand perhaps even mainly,"},{"time":208997,"text":"because they all belong to one body\nand one brain."},{"time":212324,"text":"But there's also a narrative, \na story we tell about ourselves,"},{"time":215387,"text":"the experiences we have\nwhen we remember past things."},{"time":218282,"text":"We do things because of other things."},{"time":220514,"text":"So what we desire\nis partly a result of what we believe,"},{"time":224126,"text":"and what we remember is also\ninforming us what we know."},{"time":227692,"text":"And so really, there are all these things,"},{"time":230354,"text":"like beliefs, desires, \nsensations, experiences,"},{"time":233393,"text":"they're all related to each other,"},{"time":235823,"text":"and that just is you."},{"time":239371,"text":"In some ways, it's a small difference\nfrom the common-sense understanding."},{"time":244208,"text":"In some ways, it's a massive one."}]},{"cues":[{"time":246462,"text":"It's the shift between thinking of yourself"},{"time":248638,"text":"as a thing which has \nall the experiences of life,"},{"time":252034,"text":"and thinking of yourself\nas simply that collection"},{"time":254977,"text":"of all experiences in life."},{"time":256999,"text":"You are the sum of your parts."},{"time":259847,"text":"Now those parts are also physical parts, \nof course,"},{"time":261969,"text":"brains, bodies and legs and things,"},{"time":263871,"text":"but they aren't so important, actually."},{"time":266174,"text":"If you have a heart transplant,\nyou're still the same person."},{"time":268847,"text":"If you have a memory transplant,\nare you the same person?"},{"time":271227,"text":"If you have a belief transplant, \nwould you be the same person?"},{"time":274602,"text":"Now this idea, that what we are, \nthe way to understand ourselves,"},{"time":279501,"text":"is as not of some permanent being,\nwhich has experiences,"},{"time":283962,"text":"but is kind of a collection of experiences,"},{"time":286360,"text":"might strike you as kind of weird."}]},{"cues":[{"time":288971,"text":"But actually, I don't think \nit should be weird."},{"time":291055,"text":"In a way, it's common sense."},{"time":292914,"text":"Because I just invite you \nto think about, by comparison,"},{"time":297215,"text":"think about pretty much anything else\nin the universe,"},{"time":300172,"text":"maybe apart from the \nvery most fundamental forces or powers."},{"time":302922,"text":"Let's take something like water."},{"time":305657,"text":"Now my science isn't very good."},{"time":308198,"text":"We might say something like \nwater has two parts hydrogen"},{"time":311213,"text":"and one parts oxygen, right?"},{"time":313099,"text":"We all know that."},{"time":314747,"text":"I hope no one in this room\nthinks that what that means"},{"time":318212,"text":"is there is a thing called water, \nand attached to it \n"},{"time":322414,"text":"are hydrogen and oxygen atoms,"},{"time":325051,"text":"and that's what water is."},{"time":326244,"text":"Of course we don't."},{"time":327099,"text":"We understand, very easily,\nvery straightforwardly,"},{"time":330351,"text":"that water is nothing more\n"},{"time":332083,"text":"than the hydrogen and oxygen molecules\nsuitably arranged."},{"time":337117,"text":"Everything else in the universe is the same."},{"time":339030,"text":"There's no mystery about my watch,\nfor example."},{"time":343199,"text":"We say the watch has a face, and hands,"},{"time":346562,"text":"and a mechanism and a battery,"},{"time":348362,"text":"But what we really mean is,\n"},{"time":349523,"text":"we don't think \nthere is a thing called the watch"},{"time":351128,"text":"to which we then attach all these bits."},{"time":353861,"text":"We understand very clearly \nthat you get the parts of the watch,"},{"time":356897,"text":"you put them together,\nand you create a watch."},{"time":358994,"text":"Now if everything else \nin the universe is like this,"},{"time":361638,"text":"why are we different?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":363944,"text":"Why think of ourselves"},{"time":365508,"text":"as somehow not just being \na collection of all our parts,"},{"time":369460,"text":"but somehow being a separate,\npermanent entity which has those parts?"},{"time":374328,"text":"Now this view is not particularly new, \nactually."},{"time":377438,"text":"It has quite a long lineage."},{"time":379113,"text":"You find it in Buddhism,"},{"time":380463,"text":"you find it in 17th, \n18th-century philosophy"},{"time":383009,"text":"going through to the current day,\npeople like Locke and Hume."},{"time":386604,"text":"But interestingly, it's also a view"},{"time":388687,"text":"increasingly being heard reinforced\nby neuroscience."},{"time":392731,"text":"This is Paul Broks, \nhe's a clinical neuropsychologist,"},{"time":396375,"text":"and he says this:"},{"time":397574,"text":"\"We have a deep intuition\nthat there is a core,"},{"time":399956,"text":"an essence there, \nand it's hard to shake off,"},{"time":402505,"text":"probably impossible to shake off, \nI suspect."},{"time":405516,"text":"But it's true that neuroscience shows\nthat there is no centre in the brain"},{"time":409443,"text":"where things do all come together.\""},{"time":411733,"text":"So when you look at the brain,"},{"time":414203,"text":"and you look at how the brain\nmakes possible a sense of self,"},{"time":418220,"text":"you find that there isn't \na central control spot in the brain."},{"time":422004,"text":"There is no kind of center\nwhere everything happens."},{"time":425303,"text":"There are lots of different processes\nin the brain,"},{"time":427888,"text":"all of which operate, in a way,\nquite independently."},{"time":430987,"text":"But it's because of the way \nthat they relate"},{"time":434097,"text":"that we get this sense of self."},{"time":436958,"text":"The term I use in the book, \nI call it the ego trick."},{"time":440447,"text":"It's like a mechanical trick."},{"time":445106,"text":"It's not that we don't exist,"},{"time":447586,"text":"it's just that the trick is \nto make us feel that inside of us"},{"time":450870,"text":"is something more unified\nthan is really there."}]},{"cues":[{"time":454356,"text":"Now you might think\nthis is a worrying idea."},{"time":457493,"text":"You might think that if it's true,"},{"time":459825,"text":"that for each one of us there is\nno abiding core of self,"},{"time":463576,"text":"no permanent essence,"},{"time":465561,"text":"does that mean that really,\nthe self is an illusion?"},{"time":469493,"text":"Does it mean that we really don't exist?"},{"time":471807,"text":"There is no real you."},{"time":473615,"text":"Well, a lot of people actually do use \nthis talk of illusion and so forth."},{"time":476696,"text":"These are three psychologists,\nThomas Metzinger, Bruce Hood,"},{"time":480674,"text":"Susan Blackmore,"},{"time":482978,"text":"a lot of these people do talk \nthe language of illusion,"},{"time":485963,"text":"the self is an illusion, it's a fiction."},{"time":488029,"text":"But I don't think this is \na very helpful way of looking at it."},{"time":491075,"text":"Go back to the watch."},{"time":491852,"text":"The watch isn't an illusion, \nbecause there is nothing to the watch"},{"time":495904,"text":"other than a collection of its parts."},{"time":498152,"text":"In the same way, \nwe're not illusions either."},{"time":500109,"text":"The fact that we are, in some ways,\njust this very, very complex collection,"},{"time":505552,"text":"ordered collection of things,"},{"time":507137,"text":"does not mean we're not real."},{"time":509012,"text":"I can give you \na very sort of rough metaphor for this."},{"time":511911,"text":"Let's take something like a waterfall."},{"time":514516,"text":"These are the Iguazu Falls, in Argentina."},{"time":518123,"text":"Now if you take something like this,"},{"time":520625,"text":"you can appreciate the fact \nthat in lots of ways,"},{"time":523919,"text":"there's nothing permanent about this."},{"time":526029,"text":"For one thing, it's always changing."},{"time":527462,"text":"The waters \nare always carving new channels."},{"time":530309,"text":"with changes and tides and the weather,"},{"time":532600,"text":"some things dry up, \nnew things are created."},{"time":537024,"text":"Of course the water that flows \nthrough the waterfall"},{"time":540511,"text":"is different every single instance."},{"time":543413,"text":"But it doesn't mean that \nthe Iguazu Falls are an illusion."},{"time":546165,"text":"It doesn't mean it's not real."},{"time":547798,"text":"What it means is we have \nto understand what it is"},{"time":551132,"text":"as something which has a history,"},{"time":553361,"text":"has certain things that keep it together,"},{"time":556003,"text":"but it's a process, it's fluid, \nit's forever changing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":558799,"text":"Now that, I think, is a model\nfor understanding ourselves,"},{"time":562531,"text":"and I think it's a liberating model."},{"time":564195,"text":"Because if you think that you have\nthis fixed, permanent essence,"},{"time":567231,"text":"which is always the same,\nthroughout your life, no matter what,"},{"time":570237,"text":"in a sense you're kind of trapped."},{"time":572807,"text":"You're born with an essence,"},{"time":575418,"text":"that's what you are until you die,"},{"time":578101,"text":"if you believe in an afterlife, \nmaybe you continue."},{"time":581130,"text":"But if you think of yourself\nas being, in a way,"},{"time":584100,"text":"not a thing as such, \nbut a kind of a process,"},{"time":587880,"text":"something that is changing,"},{"time":589407,"text":"then I think that's quite liberating."},{"time":590944,"text":"Because unlike the the waterfalls,"},{"time":593812,"text":"we actually have the capacity to channel"},{"time":596307,"text":"the direction of our development for ourselves\nto a certain degree."},{"time":599929,"text":"Now we've got to be careful here, right?"},{"time":602302,"text":"If you watch the X-Factor too much,\nyou might buy into this idea"},{"time":605392,"text":"that we can all be whatever we want to be."},{"time":607721,"text":"That's not true."},{"time":609039,"text":"I've heard some fantastic musicians\nthis morning,"},{"time":611209,"text":"and I am very confident\nthat I could in no way be as good as them."},{"time":614927,"text":"I could practice hard \nand maybe be good,"},{"time":617324,"text":"but I don't have\nthat really natural ability."},{"time":620328,"text":"There are limits to what we can achieve."},{"time":622985,"text":"There are limits to what \nwe can make of ourselves."},{"time":625460,"text":"But nevertheless, we do have \nthis capacity"},{"time":628122,"text":"to, in a sense, shape ourselves."},{"time":632112,"text":"The true self, as it were then,"},{"time":634368,"text":"is not something that is just there\nfor you to discover,"},{"time":638429,"text":"you don't sort of look into your soul\nand find your true self,"},{"time":642078,"text":"What you are partly doing, at least,"},{"time":643899,"text":"is actually creating your true self."},{"time":646290,"text":"And this, I think, is very,\nvery significant,"},{"time":648213,"text":"particularly at this stage of life you're at."},{"time":650179,"text":"You'll be aware of the fact"},{"time":651578,"text":"how much of you changed over recent years."},{"time":654132,"text":"If you have any videos of yourself, \nthree or four years ago,"},{"time":657371,"text":"you probably feel embarrassed \nbecause you don't recognize yourself."}]},{"cues":[{"time":660651,"text":"So I want to get that message over,\nthat what we need to do"},{"time":663532,"text":"is think about ourselves as things\nthat we can shape,"},{"time":666592,"text":"and channel and change."},{"time":667645,"text":"This is the Buddha, again:"},{"time":668941,"text":"\"Well-makers lead the water,"},{"time":671360,"text":"fletchers bend the arrow,"},{"time":672761,"text":"carpenters bend a log of wood,"},{"time":675226,"text":"wise people fashion themselves.\""},{"time":679000,"text":"And that's the idea \nI want to leave you with,"},{"time":680461,"text":"that your true self is not something \nthat you will have to go searching for,"},{"time":687668,"text":"as a mystery, and maybe never ever find."},{"time":690873,"text":"To the extent you have a true self,"},{"time":692574,"text":"it's something that you in part discover,"},{"time":695308,"text":"but in part create."},{"time":697701,"text":"and that, I think, \nis a liberating and exciting prospect."},{"time":702197,"text":"Thank you very much."}]}]}